section_text:
(a)
               

               The catchlines of the several sections of this Code are intended as mere catchwords
               to indicate the contents of the section and shall not be deemed or taken to be titles
               of such sections nor as any part of the section, nor, unless expressly so provided,
               shall they be so deemed when any of such sections, including the catchlines, are amended
               or reenacted.
               

               (b)
               

               The history notes appearing in parentheses after each section and the references and
               notes scattered throughout the Code are for the benefit of the user of the Code and
               shall have no legal effect.
